snippet: Kellen Winslow on Monday posted on Twitter which teams he thought would reach the A.F.C. championship game. Unfortunately, neither was named the Jets.
abstract: New York Jets tight end Kellen Winslow posts on Twitter which teams he thinks would reach the AFC championship game, none of which is his own team; Winslow has had difficult few weeks, with his productivity and playing time have slipping ever since he returned from a four-game suspension for violating the league’s policy on performance-enhancing substances.
lead_paragraph: Kellen Winslow on Monday posted on Twitter which teams he thought would reach the A.F.C. championship game. Unfortunately, neither was named the Jets.

headline.main: Winslow’s Prediction Is His Latest Woe
headline.print_headline: Winslow’s Prediction Is His Latest Woe
